title: Zhang Yu (hurdler)
data: Zhang Yu (Chinese: 張瑜; born 8 April 1971) is a retired female Chinese hurdler. She represented her country at the 1992 Summer Olympics.[1] Her personal best time is 12.64 seconds, achieved in September 1993 in Beijing at the 7th Chinese National Games. This is the current Chinese record.[2] This biographical article relating to People's Republic of China athletics is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
